The paper deals with face attribute transfer using generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel model that involves training a GAN, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper deals with image generation and manipulation, which is related to multimedia (MM) and graphics (GR) research.
